$ Private SQL area: persistent area
@ persistent area

The *persistent area* is part of the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA/private-SQL-area and stores values of *bind variables*.

The *persistent area* is freed when the corresponding *cursor* is closed.

The amount in bytes for the persistent area can be queried from the column `PERSISTENT_MEM` in → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/sql/diff-sql_sqlarea[`V$SQL` and `V$SQLAREA`].
